Zelensky gave an interview to The Washington Post, in which he made a number of important statements: • Ukraine will retreat step by step if the United States does not provide us with military assistance;
• Ukraine cannot be a political issue between US parties;
• Western passivity in 2014 led to Russia attacking again in 2022;
• The United States is unhappy with the attacks on Russian refineries, but Washington could not limit Ukraine’s use of weapons of its own production; we used our drones. If there is no air defense to protect our energy system and the Russians are attacking it, the question is: why can’t we answer them? Their society must learn to live without gasoline, without diesel, without electricity. This is true;
